# TypeScript Rules — mortgage-intelligence

## Type Safety
- `strict: true` is enabled — never use `any` unless unavoidable and annotated with a comment
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` for untyped external data
- Use `satisfies` operator for type-safe object literals
- Export types and interfaces from a co-located `types.ts` when shared across files

## React / Next.js
- Use Next.js App Router (`app/` directory) — no Pages Router
- Server Components by default — add `'use client'` only when needed
- Use `next/image` for all images, `next/link` for all internal navigation
- Data fetching in Server Components — avoid client-side fetch waterfalls
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` for async route segments

## API Routes
- Use Next.js Route Handlers (`app/api/.../route.ts`)
- Always validate request bodies with Zod
- Return typed `Response` objects

## File Naming
- Component files: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Route files: Next.js conventions (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `route.ts`)
- Utility files: `camelCase.ts`
- Type definition files: `types.ts`

## Environment Variables
- Prefix client-accessible vars with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
- Never expose secrets to the client bundle
